cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the management of traffic in ATM networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). It also discusses the rules that sources have to follow to achieve a fair and efficient allocation of network resources, which involves the use of algorithms and protocols for traffic management (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the monitoring of network traffic and the provision of feedback to end systems, which relates to network security and intrusion detection (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of ABR service for data applications, which involves multimedia data transmission (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the behavior of sources in the context of network resource allocation, which involves the study of distributed systems and algorithms (cs.DC).
